{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "The evolutionary view on human nature sells humanity short.", "abstract": "David Brooks Op-Ed column examines literature on the chemistry and biology of love and sex; says it seems to reinforce an evolutionary view of human nature, in which humans have two systems, one unconscious and one rational; contends such a view sells humanity short, leaving the impression that humans are just slightly higher animals, and lopping off entire regions of human possibility.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "27", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "David", "role": "reported", "lastname": "BROOKS", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By DAVID BROOKS", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/14/opinion/brooks-the-deepest-self.html", "lead_paragraph": "The evolutionary view on human nature sells humanity short.", "headline": {"main": "The Deepest Self", "print_headline": "The Deepest Self", "content_kicker": "Op-Ed Columnist", "kicker": "Op-Ed Columnist"}, "_id": "5322518338f0d8378edc9c84", "word_count": "808", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New/Brooks_New-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New/Brooks_New-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 900, "url": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New/Brooks_New-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New/Brooks_New-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "900"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New/Brooks_New-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2010/09/16/opinion/Brooks_New/Brooks_New-thumbStandard.jpg", "thumbnailwidth": "75", "thumbnailheight": "75"}, "subtype": "thumbnail", "width": 75, "type": "image"}], "pub_date": "2014-03-14T00:00: